Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, sprinkle over the @black sesame seeds{5%grams}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast the wedges on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, zest and quarter the @lime{1} into wedges.

In a small #bowl{}, combine the @breadcrumbs{25%grams}, lime zest, @olive oil{1%tbsp} and a pinch of salt and pepper. Set aside.

In a medium bowl, combine the @coleslaw mix{120%grams}, half the @mango chutney{40%grams}, half the @mayonnaise{64%grams} and a good squeeze of lime juice. Season with salt and pepper, mix well then set aside.

Pat the @sea bass fillets{2} dry with #kitchen paper{}, then lay onto a lined baking tray. Sprinkle over the @Caribbean style jerk{1%sachet}, drizzle with oil, season with salt and pepper, then rub to coat.

> Caribbean Style Jerk seasoning contains paprika, cayenne, pimento and thyme.

Spread the remaining mayonnaise over the top of the fish and top with the zesty breadcrumbs. Gently press down with a #spoon{} to secure.

Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until golden and cooked through, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. It's cooked when opaque in the middle.

Share the sea bass between your plates. Serve the wedges and slaw alongside.

Drizzle the remaining mango chutney over the sea bass to finish. Serve with any remaining lime wedges for squeezing over.

Enjoy!